---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
const title = `Editorial Standards — ${SITE.name}`;
const description = 'How Texas AI Report sources, verifies, and edits its reporting.';
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="col" style="padding-top:40px;padding-bottom:48px">
    <div class="kicker">Editorial Standards</div>
    <h1 style="margin:8px 0 24px;color:var(--navy)">Editorial Standards</h1>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-bottom:8px">Independence</h2>
    <p>
      Coverage decisions at Texas AI Report are made by the editor without
      direction from advertisers, sponsors, or affiliated commercial entities.
      The publication is affiliated with ModalPoint through common ownership, and
      ModalPoint is its launch sponsor; when a story touches ModalPoint, the
      relationship is disclosed within the story itself.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-top:32px;margin-bottom:8px">Sourcing</h2>
    <p>
      Reporting is built from primary sources: legislation and regulatory filings,
      official agency documents, peer-reviewed research, court records, and
      on-record statements from named individuals or organizations. Secondary
      sources are cited and linked. We do not publish claims we cannot trace to
      a verifiable primary source.
    </p>
    <p>
      Material facts — statistics, funding figures, company facts, statements of
      law or policy, and attributed quotes — are corroborated against at least
      three independent, citable sources before publication. A claim that rests on
      a single source is labeled as such, or held until it can be corroborated.
    </p>
    <p>
      For legal and regulatory stories, facts are checked against primary
      government or judicial sources before publication.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-top:32px;margin-bottom:8px">AI-Assisted Workflow</h2>
    <p>
      Texas AI Report uses an AI-assisted newsroom workflow to research, draft,
      and organize facts. <strong>Before anything publishes, every material claim
      must clear a fact-check gate — corroborated against at least three
      independent, citable sources, with nothing published that we cannot trace to
      resolvable sources.</strong> We never publish an AI-generated fact, quote, or
      statistic that isn't independently sourced. Editorial oversight sits over the
      process, and higher-stakes legal and regulatory items receive additional
      human review.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-top:32px;margin-bottom:8px">Analysis vs. Legal Advice</h2>
    <p>
      Texas AI Report provides analysis and commentary on AI law, policy, and
      regulation. Nothing published here constitutes legal advice. Readers
      facing legal questions should consult a qualified attorney.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:18px;margin-top:32px;margin-bottom:8px">Corrections</h2>
    <p>
      We correct errors promptly and transparently. See our
      <a href="/corrections">Corrections policy</a> for how to request a
      correction and how corrections are marked on published articles.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
